cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC. 

The paper focuses on building a visual encoding model using deep neural networks and transfer learning to predict cortical responses in a functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) dataset. This involves incorporating a pre-trained DNN (i.e., AlexNet) and training a nonlinear mapping from visual features to brain activity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also involves training a nonlinear mapping, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of transfer learning also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the focus on brain-machine interfaces suggests that it could also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
